>
  <h2>The question</h2>
  <p>Which vision language fusion strategy is most effective for Visual Question Answering (VQA) when compute is constrained?</p>

  <h2>What I built</h2>
  <p>I conducted an empirical comparison of four fusion strategies on the VQA v2 dataset. To enable efficient fine-tuning, I implemented LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) from scratch, targeting only 0.19% of total parameters.</p>

  <h2>What I found</h2>
  <p>Cross-attention fusion outperformed simple concatenation and gated mechanisms. The scratch built LoRA implementation achieved 98% of full fine-tuning performance without any catastrophic forgetting.</p>
